.TH "fpga_mgr_lock" 9 "fpga_mgr_lock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fpga_mgr_lock \- Lock FPGA manager for exclusive use
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fpga_mgr_lock
.BI "(struct fpga_manager *mgr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mgr" 12
fpga manager
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Given a pointer to FPGA Manager (from \fBfpga_mgr_get\fP or
\fBof_fpga_mgr_put\fP) attempt to get the mutex. The user should call
\fBfpga_mgr_lock\fP and verify that it returns 0 before attempting to
program the FPGA.  Likewise, the user should call fpga_mgr_unlock
when done programming the FPGA.
.SH "RETURN"
0 for success or -EBUSY
